## Required Structure

**⚠️ CRITICAL: All feature logic MUST be in `app/(app)/{feature_name}/_{feature_name}/`**

Create the following structure, replacing `{feature}` and `{Feature}` appropriately (e.g., `products`, `Product`):

```
app/(app)/{feature-name}/
├── page.tsx                    # Main list/page component (thin wrapper)
├── create/
│   └── page.tsx               # Create page (minimal wrapper)
├── [{resource_info}]/         # Dynamic route for resource details
│   ├── profile/
│   │   └── page.tsx           # Profile/detail page (server component)
│   ├── edit-{resource}/
│   │   └── page.tsx           # Edit resource page (thin wrapper)
│   ├── add-{nested-resource}/
│   │   └── page.tsx           # Add nested resource page (thin wrapper)
│   └── edit-{nested-resource}/
│       └── [{nested_id}]/
│           └── page.tsx       # Edit nested resource page (thin wrapper)
└── _{feature-name}/           # ⚠️ ALL FEATURE LOGIC GOES HERE
    ├── columns/               # DataTable column definitions
    │   └── {resource}-columns.tsx
    │   # For multi-resource features: cities-columns.tsx, states-columns.tsx, etc.
    ├── components/            # Shared feature components
    │   └── {resource}-header-buttons.tsx
    ├── form-options/          # Form configuration and schemas
    │   └── {resource}-form-options.ts
    │   # For multi-resource features: cities-form-options.tsx, states-form-options.tsx, etc.
    ├── forms/                 # Form components and field groups
    │   ├── {resource}-form.tsx
    │   └── {section-name}.tsx
    │   # For multi-resource features: organize by resource in subfolders
    │   # forms/cities/, forms/states/, forms/countries/
    ├── hooks/                 # Custom hooks with barrel export
    │   ├── index.ts
    │   └── {feature}-params.ts
    │   # For multi-resource features: cities-params.ts, states-params.ts, etc.
    ├── tables/                # Table components
    │   └── {resource}-table.tsx
    │   # For multi-resource features: cities-table.tsx, states-table.tsx, etc.
    ├── tabs/                  # Tab components
    │   └── {tab-name}-tab.tsx
    └── types/                 # TypeScript type definitions
        └── tabs-types.ts

query/{feature-name}/          # Query layer (separate from app folder)
├── {feature-name}-types.ts    # Entity types (all resources in one file for multi-resource features)
├── {feature-name}-query.ts    # queryOptions + get/list/detail (all resources)
├── {feature-name}-mutations.ts # mutationOptions (all resources)
└── index.ts                   # Barrel exports
```

## Private Feature Folder (`_{feature-name}/`)

**⚠️ CRITICAL: This folder contains ALL feature logic. Pages are thin wrappers only.**

The private folder (prefixed with underscore) contains all shared components, utilities, and configurations for the feature. **DO NOT** place business logic in page files - always extract to `_{feature_name}/`.

### Directory Purposes:

- **`columns/`**: DataTable column definitions
  - Each table should have its own column file
  - Naming: `{resource}-columns.tsx`
  - Export column hook: `use{Resource}Columns()` (must be a hook, see [data-table.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-components/data-table.mdc))

- **`components/`**: Shared feature components
  - Reusable components specific to the feature
  - Examples: header buttons, modals, custom UI elements
  - Naming: `{resource}-{purpose}.tsx`
  - **⚠️ CRITICAL: For delete dialogs, ALWAYS use `useRowActions` hook which handles delete dialog internally**
    - **DO NOT manually render `DeleteConfirmationDialog`** - The hook returns `deleteDialog` to pass as prop to `DataTable`
    - **DO NOT create custom delete dialog wrapper components** - Use `useRowActions` hook pattern
    - **DO NOT manually manage delete state** - Hook handles `deleteItem` and `deleteOpen` internally
    - Only create custom delete dialogs if there's specific business logic that cannot be handled by the standard dialog (e.g., deactivate vs delete with different flows)
    - See [data-table.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-components/data-table.mdc) for the standard delete dialog pattern

- **`form-options/`**: Form configuration and validation schemas
  - Uses `formOptions` from `@tanstack/react-form`
  - Includes Zod validation schemas
  - Naming: `{resource}-form-options.tsx` or `{resource}-form-options.ts`

- **`forms/`**: Form components and field groups
  - Main form component: `{resource}-form.tsx`
  - Field groups: `{section-name}.tsx` (e.g., `basic-info.tsx`, `contact.tsx`)
  - Uses `withForm` HOC for field components

- **`hooks/`**: Custom hooks
  - Must include `index.ts` barrel export
  - Examples: URL params hooks, feature-specific hooks
  - Naming: `{purpose}-hook.ts` or `{feature}-{purpose}.ts`
  - **ALWAYS create query parameters in the `{feature}-params.ts` hook**. The hook must return a `standardQueryParams` object containing **ONLY** `page`, `per_page`, and `search`. Additional filters should be returned separately and combined when needed. **DO NOT** create query params objects inline in components or tabs. See [data-table.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-components/data-table.mdc) for the Query Params Hook Pattern.

- **`tables/`**: Table components
  - Reusable table components for the feature
  - Naming: `{resource}-table.tsx`
  - Uses DataTable components

- **`tabs/`**: Tab components
  - Components used in tabbed interfaces
  - Naming: `{tab-name}-tab.tsx`

- **`types/`**: TypeScript type definitions
  - Shared types for the feature
  - Naming: `{purpose}-types.ts`

## Generation Requirements

- **React Query (required)**
  - Use `queryOptions` for queries and wrap with `useQuery` in components.
  - For mutations, create `mutationOptions` exports (e.g., `create{Feature}MutationOptions`, `update{Feature}MutationOptions`, `delete{Feature}MutationOptions`) with `meta.invalidatesQuery` keys for list/detail. See [react-query.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-layer/react-query.mdc) for pattern.
  - Use project `fetcher<T>()` and `auth: true` where appropriate.
  - Use query keys consistent with `query-client/query.d.ts` and existing patterns.
  - When extending user-related functionality (e.g., riders or their parents), reuse the existing `'users'` query key root. Do **not** add new root keys such as `'riders-*'`; instead append segments (`['users', 'parents', riderId]`).
  - When types already live in another feature (e.g., `query/users/users-types.ts` provides `Parent`), extend that module instead of introducing a parallel `query/{feature}` directory.

- **TanStack Table (required)**
  - Create `{feature}-columns.tsx` in `_{feature}/columns/` exporting `use{Resource}Columns()` hook that returns `ColumnDef<{Feature}>[]` with sensible columns and an `actions` column using `DataTableRowActions` and `createRowActions`.
  - Create `{feature}-table.tsx` in `_{feature}/tables/` that:
    - Calls `useQuery(get{FeaturePlural}Options(...))` from the query layer.
    - Uses `useDataTable` to configure pagination, sorting, and pinning; passes data and columns to shared `DataTable`.
  - Row actions should `router.push` to `/{feature}/{id}/edit` rather than opening in-place modals by default.

- **TanStack Form (required)**
  - In `form-options/{feature}-form-options.ts`, define a Zod schema and a `formOptions` factory for create/edit.
  - In `forms/{feature}-form.tsx`, initialize with `useAppForm({ ...{Feature}FormOptions(data), validators: { onChange: schema } })` and wire submit to mutation hooks from query layer.

- **Permissions (recommended)**
  - Use `usePermissions()` and `PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_CREATE|UPDATE|DESTROY` to guard actions (buttons, row actions, submit buttons).

## Inter-Rule References (must follow)

- **Use the react-query rule** for all data fetching and mutations. Do not inline fetch calls in components.
- **Use the data-table rule** to build columns and table; pass query hook data and `columns` to the shared `DataTable`.
- **Use the tanstack-form rule** to build form options and form; submit via mutation hooks.
- **Use the permission-system rule** to wrap or disable UI elements based on required permissions.

## Page Patterns

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Pages should be THIN WRAPPERS. All logic goes in `_{feature_name}/`**

### 1. Main List Page (`page.tsx`)

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Main list pages MUST follow this exact pattern:**

- Page is a **server component** (async function, no `'use client'`)
- Page MUST include `PageHeader` component with `title` and `description`
- Client component (table) MUST accept `className` prop
- **⚠️ CRITICAL: Pass `className="m-5"` to the table component when it's a direct child of PageHeader (no tabs)**
- **⚠️ CRITICAL: Do NOT pass `className="m-5"` when table is inside TabsContent (tabs handle spacing)**
- Client component MUST use `cn()` utility to merge `className` with base classes

```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next'

import { {Resource}Table } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/tables/{resource}-table'
import {PageHeader} from '@/components/custom/page-header'

export default async function {Resource}TablePage() {
  return (
    <>
      <PageHeader description="Manage and view {Resources}" title="{Resources}" />
      <{Resource}Table className="m-5" />
    </>
  )
}

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    description: 'Manage and view {Resources}',
    title: '{Resources}'
  }
}
```

**Client Component Pattern (Table Component):**

The table component MUST accept `className` prop and use `cn()` to merge it. The `toolbar` prop MUST be passed to `DataTable`, and `main` must use `className={cn('relative', className)}`:

```tsx
'use client'

import { cn } from '@/utils'
import { DataTable, DataTableToolbar } from '@/components/data-table'

export const {Resource}Table: React.FC<{ className?: string }> = ({
  className
}) => {
  // ... table logic ...

  return (
    <main className={cn('relative', className)}>
      <DataTable
        toolbar={
          <DataTableToolbar
            createButtonHref="/{feature}/create"
            table={table}
          />
        }
        table={table}
      />
    </main>
  )
}
```

**OR** if the page needs to handle routing/params directly:

```tsx
'use client'

import React from 'react'
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query'

import {PageHeader} from '@/components/custom/page-header'
import { DataTable, DataTableToolbar, DataTableViewOptions } from '@/components/data-table'
import { useDataTable } from '@/hooks/use-data-table'
import { useRowActions } from '@/hooks/use-row-actions'

import { use{Resource}Columns } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/columns/{resource}-columns'
import { use{Feature}Params } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/hooks'
import { PERMISSIONS } from '@/lib/auth/permissions'
import { getAll{Resource}Query, delete{Resource}MutationOptions } from '@/query/{feature}'

export default function {Resource}TablePage() {
  const { standardQueryParams, status, type } = use{Feature}Params()
  const { data: {resources}, isLoading, isError, error, refetch } = useQuery(
    getAll{Resource}Query({ ...standardQueryParams, ...(type && { type }), ...(status && { status }) })
  )

  const { deleteDialog, permissions, setRowAction } = useRowActions<{Resource}>({
    deleteDialogConfig: {
      description: 'Are you sure you want to delete this {resource}?',
      getItemName: ({resource}) => {resource}.name,
      title: 'Delete {Resource}'
    },
    deleteMutationOptions: delete{Resource}MutationOptions,
    permissions: {
      delete: PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_DESTROY,
      update: PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_UPDATE,
      view: PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_SHOW
    },
    redirectOnUpdate: ({resource}) => `/{feature}/${resource}.id}/edit`,
    redirectOnView: ({resource}) => `/{feature}/${resource}.id}/profile`
  })

  const columns = use{Resource}Columns({
    permissions,
    setRowAction
  })

  const { table } = useDataTable({
    clearOnDefault: true,
    columns,
    data: {resources}?.data?.data || [],
    getRowId: (originalRow) => `${originalRow.id}`,
    initialState: {
      columnPinning: { right: ['actions'] },
      pagination: {
        pageIndex: {resources}?.data?.pagination?.current_page || 0,
        pageSize: {resources}?.data?.pagination?.per_page || 15
      },
      sorting: [{ desc: true, id: 'id' }]
    },
    pageCount: {resources}?.data?.pagination?.last_page || 0,
    rowCount: {resources}?.data?.pagination?.total || 0
  })

  return (
    <>
      <PageHeader
        description="Manage {resource} information"
        title="{Resources}"
      />
      <main className={cn('relative', className)}>
        <DataTable
          deleteDialog={deleteDialog}
          error={error}
          isError={isError}
          isLoading={isLoading}
          refetch={refetch}
          toolbar={
            <DataTableToolbar
              createButtonHref="/{feature}/create"
              filters={[
                {
                  key: 'type',
                  label: 'Type',
                  options: [
                    { key: 'option1', label: 'Option 1', value: '1' },
                    { key: 'option2', label: 'Option 2', value: '2' }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  key: 'status',
                  label: 'Status',
                  options: [
                    { key: 'active', label: 'Active', value: '1' },
                    { key: 'inactive', label: 'Inactive', value: '0' }
                  ]
                }
              ]}
              permissions={{
                create: PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_CREATE
              }}
              searchPlaceholder="Search {resources}"
              table={table}
            />
          }
          table={table}
        />
      </main>
    </>
  )
}

// Note: This example assumes className is passed as prop. For page components, use the pattern shown in the table component example above.
```

### 2. Create Page (`create/page.tsx`)

Minimal wrapper that renders the form component from `_{feature}/forms/`.

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Form pages MUST pass `className="m-5"` to form components when they are direct children of PageHeader (not inside tabs):**

- **✅ DO**: Pass `className="m-5"` when form is direct child of `PageHeader` (no tabs)
- **❌ DON'T**: Pass `className="m-5"` when form is inside `TabsContent` (tabs handle spacing)

```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next'

import { {Resource}Form } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/forms/{resource}-form'

export default async function Create{Resource}Page() {
  return <{Resource}Form className="m-5" />
}

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    description: 'Create a new {resource}',
    title: 'Create {Resource}'
  }
}
```

### 3. Edit Page (`[{resource_info}]/edit-{resource}/page.tsx`)

Thin wrapper that prefetches resource data on the server and lets the client form read it via `useQuery`.

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Form pages MUST pass `className="m-5"` to form components when they are direct children of PageHeader (not inside tabs):**

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Server component MUST use `prefetchQuery` with try-catch for edit pages and pass only identifiers/flags to the client form (not the fetched entity). The client form MUST call `useQuery` directly.**

```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next'
import { dehydrate, HydrationBoundary } from '@tanstack/react-query'

import { getQueryClient } from '@/query-client'
import { get{Resource}ByIdQuery } from '@/query/{feature}'
import { {Resource}Form } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/forms/{resource}-form'

type {Resource}EditPageProps = {
  params: Promise<{
    {resource_info}: string
  }>
}

export default async function {Resource}EditPage({
  params
}: {Resource}EditPageProps) {
  const { {resource_info} } = await params
  const id = {resource_info}.split('-').at(-1)
  const queryClient = getQueryClient()

  // Pre-fetch data on server with error handling
  try {
    await queryClient.prefetchQuery(get{Resource}ByIdQuery(id))
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error)
  }

  return (
    <HydrationBoundary state={dehydrate(queryClient)}>
      <{Resource}Form className="m-5" isEdit {resource}Id={id} />
    </HydrationBoundary>
  )
}

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    description: 'Edit {resource}',
    title: 'Edit {Resource}'
  }
}
```

### 4. Profile/Detail Page (`[{resource_info}]/profile/page.tsx`)

Server component that prefetches data and displays tabs. Tab components come from `_{feature}/tabs/`.

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Server component MUST use `prefetchQuery` with try-catch and `HydrationBoundary`**

**⚠️ MANDATORY: Client/child components MUST use `useQuery` directly - they should NOT access data from server prefetch**

**⚠️ IMPORTANT: When using reusable client components that need mutations (e.g., `HeaderActions` with toggle mutations), pass mutation options from the query layer**:

```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next'
import { dehydrate, HydrationBoundary } from '@tanstack/react-query'

import { NotFound } from '@/components/ui/not-found'
import { getQueryClient } from '@/query-client'
import { get{Resource}ByIdQuery } from '@/query/{feature}'
import { {Resource}Tabs } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/tabs/{resource}-tabs'

type {Resource}InfoPageProps = {
  params: Promise<{
    {resource_info}: string
  }>
}

export async function generateMetadata({
  params
}: {Resource}InfoPageProps): Promise<Metadata> {
  const { {resource_info} } = await params
  const id = {resource_info}.split('-').at(-1)
  const queryClient = getQueryClient()
  let {resource}

  try {
    const result = await queryClient.fetchQuery(get{Resource}ByIdQuery(id))
    {resource} = result.data
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error)
  }

  return {
    description: {resource}?.email || 'View {resource} details',
    title: {resource}?.name || '{Resource} Details'
  }
}

export default async function {Resource}InfoPage({ params }: {Resource}InfoPageProps) {
  const { {resource_info} } = await params
  const id = {resource_info}.split('-').at(-1)

  if (!id) {
    return <NotFound title="{Resource} not found" />
  }

  const queryClient = getQueryClient()

  // Pre-fetch data on server with error handling
  try {
    await queryClient.prefetchQuery(get{Resource}ByIdQuery(id))
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error)
  }

  // Wrap client component with HydrationBoundary to pass dehydrated state
  return (
    <HydrationBoundary state={dehydrate(queryClient)}>
      <{Resource}Tabs {resource}Id={id} />
    </HydrationBoundary>
  )
}
```

**⚠️ MANDATORY: Client Component Pattern - MUST use `useQuery` directly**

```tsx
'use client'

import { HeaderActions } from '@/components/custom/header-actions'
import {PageHeader} from '@/components/custom/page-header'
import { NotFound } from '@/components/ui/not-found'
import { Tabs, TabsContent, TabsList, TabsTrigger } from '@/components/ui/tabs'
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query'

import { {NestedResource}Table } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/tables/{nested-resource}-table'
import { {Tab}Tab } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/tabs/{tab-name}-tab'
import { PERMISSIONS } from '@/lib/auth/permissions'
import { get{Resource}ByIdQuery, toggle{Resource}StatusMutationOptions } from '@/query/{feature}'

type {Resource}TabsProps = {
  {resource}Id: string | number
}

export const {Resource}Tabs: React.FC<{Resource}TabsProps> = ({ {resource}Id }) => {
  // ✅ CORRECT: Client component MUST use useQuery directly
  // The prefetched data from server is automatically used via HydrationBoundary
  const { data: {resource}, isLoading, isError } = useQuery(get{Resource}ByIdQuery({resource}Id))

  if (!{resource} || isError) {
    return <NotFound title="{Resource} not found" />
  }

  return (
    <>
      <PageHeader
        badge={resource?.badge}
        image={resource?.image_url || undefined}
        title={resource?.name}
      >
        <HeaderActions
          activeToggleMutation={{
            mutationFnParam: {resource}Id,
            mutationOptions: toggle{Resource}StatusMutationOptions
          }}
          editPath={`/{feature}/edit/${resource}Id}`}
          editPermissionKey={PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_UPDATE}
          initialStatus={resource?.status === 1}
          email={resource?.email}
          phone={resource?.phone}
        />
      </PageHeader>
      <Tabs defaultValue="profile" useUrlState>
        <TabsList>
          <TabsTrigger value="profile">Profile</TabsTrigger>
          <TabsTrigger value="{tab1}">{Tab1}</TabsTrigger>
          <TabsTrigger value="{tab2}">{Tab2}</TabsTrigger>
        </TabsList>

        <TabsContent value="profile">
          <{NestedResource}Table
            {resource}Id={resource}Id}
            {resource}Name={resource.name}
          />
        </TabsContent>

        <TabsContent value="{tab1}">
          <{Tab}Tab {resource}Id={resource}Id} />
        </TabsContent>
      </Tabs>
    </>
  )
}
```

**Pattern for reusable mutation components**:

- Export `mutationOptions` from query layer (see [react-query.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-layer/react-query.mdc) for pattern)
- Pass `{ mutationFnParam: id, mutationOptions: toggle{Resource}StatusMutationOptions }` to client components
- Client components use `useMutation(mutationOptions)` internally
- This allows the same component to work with different mutations across features

### 5. Add Nested Resource Page (`[{resource_info}]/add-{nested-resource}/page.tsx`)

Thin wrapper that extracts parent resource info and renders nested form from `_{feature}/forms/`.

```tsx
import { NotFound } from '@/components/ui/not-found'

import { {NestedResource}Form } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/forms/{nested-resource}-form'

type Add{NestedResource}PageProps = {
  params: Promise<{
    {resource_info}: string
  }>
}

export default async function Add{NestedResource}Page({ params }: Add{NestedResource}PageProps) {
  const { {resource_info} } = await params
  const {resource}Id = decodeURIComponent({resource_info}).split('-').at(-1)
  const {resource}Name = decodeURIComponent({resource_info})
    .split('-')
    .slice(0, -2)
    .join('-')

  if (!{resource}Id) {
    return <NotFound title="{Resource} not found" />
  }

  return <{NestedResource}Form {resource}Id={{resource}Id} {resource}Name={{resource}Name} />
}
```

## Component Patterns

All components MUST be in `_{feature_name}/`. Pages are thin wrappers only.

### 1. Column Definitions (`_{feature}/columns/{resource}-columns.tsx`)

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Columns MUST be custom hooks. See [data-table.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-components/data-table.mdc) for details.**

**⚠️ CRITICAL: ALL cell renderers MUST use `Column.{Component}` from `@/components/data-table/columns`. Never use raw HTML elements (`<div>`, `<span>`) or direct component imports (`<Chip>`, `<Avatar>`) in cell renderers. See [data-table.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-components/data-table.mdc) "Column Cell Components" section for complete documentation.**

```tsx
'use client'

import { useMemo } from 'react'
import { ColumnDef } from '@tanstack/react-table'

import { Column } from '@/components/data-table/columns'
import { DataTableColumnHeader } from '@/components/data-table/data-table-column-header'
import {
  createRowActions,
  DataTableRowActions
} from '@/components/data-table/data-table-row-actions'

import { {Resource} } from '@/query/{feature}/{feature}-types'
import { DataTableRowAction } from '@/types/data-table'

type {Resource}ColumnsProps = {
  permissions?: {
    delete?: boolean
    edit?: boolean
    view?: boolean
  }
  setRowAction: (rowAction?: DataTableRowAction<{Resource}> | null) => void
}

export function use{Resource}Columns({
  permissions = {
    delete: true,
    edit: true,
    view: true
  },
  setRowAction
}: {Resource}ColumnsProps): ColumnDef<{Resource}>[] {
  return useMemo(
    () => [
      {
        accessorKey: 'id',
        cell: ({ row }) => (
          <Column.Text
            text={row.original.id.toString().padStart(2, '0')}
            variant="id"
          />
        ),
        enableHiding: true,
        header: ({ column }) => (
          <DataTableColumnHeader column={column} title="ID" />
        ),
        id: 'id',
        size: 80
      },
      {
        accessorKey: 'name',
        cell: ({ row }) => <Column.Text text={row.original.name} />,
        enableColumnFilter: true,
        enableHiding: true,
        header: ({ column }) => (
          <DataTableColumnHeader column={column} title="Name" />
        ),
        id: 'name'
      },
      {
        cell: ({ row }) => (
          <DataTableRowActions
            actions={createRowActions({
              delete: permissions.delete
                ? {
                    hidden: () => !permissions.delete,
                    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'delete' })
                  }
                : undefined,
              edit: permissions.edit
                ? {
                    hidden: () => !permissions.edit,
                    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'update' })
                  }
                : undefined,
              view: permissions.view
                ? {
                    hidden: () => !permissions.view,
                    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'view' })
                  }
                : undefined
            })}
            row={row}
          />
        ),
        enableHiding: false,
        header: () => <div className="text-center font-semibold">Actions</div>,
        id: 'actions',
        size: 150
      }
    ],
    [permissions, setRowAction]
  )
}
```

### 2. Form Options (`_{feature}/form-options/{resource}-form-options.tsx`)

```tsx
import { formOptions } from '@tanstack/react-form'
import { z } from 'zod'

import { {Resource}ById } from '@/query/{feature}'

export const {Resource}FormOptions = ({resource}?: {Resource}ById) =>
  formOptions({
    defaultValues: {
      name: {resource}?.name || '',
      email: {resource}?.email || '',
      status: {resource}?.status === 1 ? true : false
    } as Create{Resource}Schema
  })

export const create{Resource}Schema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, { message: 'Name is required' }),
  email: z.string().email({ message: 'Invalid email format' }),
  status: z.boolean()
})

export type Create{Resource}Schema = z.infer<typeof create{Resource}Schema>
```

### 3. Main Form Component (`_{feature}/forms/{resource}-form.tsx`)

```tsx
import {PageHeader} from '@/components/custom/page-header'
import { useAppForm } from '@/components/form'
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card'

import { usePermissions } from '@/hooks/use-permissions'

import {
  create{Resource}Schema,
  {Resource}FormOptions
} from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/form-options/{resource}-form-options'
import { BasicInfoFields } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/forms/basic-info'
import { ContactFields } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/forms/contact'
import { PERMISSIONS } from '@/lib/auth/permissions'
import {
  useCreate{Resource}Mutation,
  useUpdate{Resource}Mutation
} from '@/query/{feature}/{feature}-mutations'
import { {Resource}ById } from '@/query/{feature}/{feature}-types'
import { apiFormValidation } from '@/utils'

type {Resource}FormProps = {
  isEdit?: boolean
  {resource}?: {Resource}ById
}

export const {Resource}Form: React.FC<{Resource}FormProps> = ({
  isEdit = false,
  {resource}
}) => {
  const { hasPermission } = usePermissions()
  const { isPending: isCreating, mutateAsync: create{Resource} } =
    useCreate{Resource}Mutation()

  const { isPending: isUpdating, mutateAsync: update{Resource} } =
    useUpdate{Resource}Mutation()

  const form = useAppForm({
    ...{Resource}FormOptions({resource}),
    onSubmit: async ({ formApi, value }) => {
      apiFormValidation(
        () =>
          isEdit
            ? update{Resource}({
                ...value,
                id: {resource}?.id,
                status: value.status ? 1 : 0
              })
            : create{Resource}({ ...value, status: value.status ? 1 : 0 }),
        formApi
      )
    },
    validators: {
      onChange: create{Resource}Schema
    }
  })

  return (
    <>
      <PageHeader
        description="Add a new {resource} to the system"
        title={isEdit ? 'Edit {Resource}' : 'Create {Resource}'}
      >
        <form.AppForm>
          <form.SubmitButton
            disabled={
              isEdit
                ? !hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_UPDATE)
                : !hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.{FEATURE}_CREATE)
            }
            form="create-{resource}-form"
            isLoading={isEdit ? isUpdating : isCreating}
          >
            {isEdit ? 'Update {Resource}' : 'Create {Resource}'}
          </form.SubmitButton>
        </form.AppForm>
      </PageHeader>
      <div className="m-5 flex">
        <form
          className="w-full flex-1 space-y-5"
          id="create-{resource}-form"
          onSubmit={(e) => {
            e.preventDefault()
            form.handleSubmit()
          }}
        >
          <Card id="basic-info">
            <CardHeader>
              <CardTitle>Basic Info</CardTitle>
            </CardHeader>
            <CardContent>
              <BasicInfoFields form={form} />
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
          <Card id="contact">
            <CardHeader>
              <CardTitle>Contact</CardTitle>
            </CardHeader>
            <CardContent>
              <ContactFields form={form} />
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
        </form>
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

